OL,6,FTributes have been paid to the former
OL,7,Fhead of the Northern Ireland Civil
OL,8,FService Sir Kenneth Bloomfield, who
OL,9,Fhas died at the age of 94.
OL,11,FHealth Minister Mike Nesbitt described
OL,12,FSir Kenneth as a "great intellect" and
OL,13,F"one of our finest".
OL,15,FHis career in public service began in
OL,16,Fthe 1950s and he was cabinet secretary
OL,17,Fto the 1974 Stormont powersharing
OL,18,Fexecutive, and head of the NI Civil
OL,19,FService from 1984 to 1991.
